The paper deals with natural language processing and deep learning techniques for sentence extraction from scientific articles. The use of attention-based models and LSTM-based sequence encoders suggests a focus on language modeling and text classification, which are common topics in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL). Additionally, the use of topic models for context embedding suggests a potential interest in unsupervised learning and topic modeling, which are also common in these sub-categories.
